http__purl_org_dc_terms_description: Trait that describes the size class of an organism.

http__www_w3_org_2004_02_skos_core_defin: Individual organisms with a mean body size between 2.0 and 200 mm (as defined, agreed and applied by the WoRMS Steering Committee).
Individual organisms with a mean body size smaller than 0.2 mm (as defined, agreed and applied by the WoRMS Steering Committee).
Individual organisms with a mean body size larger than 200 mm (as defined, agreed and applied by the WoRMS Steering Committee).
Individual organisms with a mean body size between 0.2 and 2.0 mm (as defined, agreed and applied by the WoRMS Steering Committee).
